    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.35b.20"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">20</fw>
                
                <fw type="imprint">
                    <unclear>Sunbeam</unclear> 
                        <lb/>
                    <hi rend="caps">TELEVISION 
                        <lb/>
                    CORPORATION 
                        <lb/>
                        
                    WCKT CHANNEL 7 KBC <unclear/></hi>
                        <lb/>
                    
                    1401 79th Street Causeway 
                        <lb/>
                    Miami, Florida 33138
                        <lb/>
                    Phone 305-751-6692
                        <lb/>
                    
                    <figure>
                        <figDesc>Photograph of WCKT Television Station</figDesc>
                    </figure> 
                        <lb/>
                    
                    <hi rend="italics">On Broadcast Key... America's Most Beautiful Television Station</hi> 
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>August 13, 1971</dateline> 
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John Neihardt</addrLine> 
                        <addrLine>Skyrim, <hi rend="caps">R.D.</hi> 7</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Columbia, Missouri</addrLine>
                    </address>
                
                    <note>Ansd 9-3-71</note> 
                
                    <salute>Sir:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I have been wanting to write you for some time, since your appearance on the Dick Cavett show. I listened with great interest, to your stories of Black Elk and especially to your words on the death of Crazy Horse. Since then, I have been looking for your works at local bookstores and libraries, to no avail.</p> 
                
                <p>If you will forgive the imposition, I would like to know how I could obtain copies of the work on Crazy Horse, as well as "Black Elk Speaks."</p>
                
                <p>Having been born on a Seneca reservation, and possessing an avid interest in Indian lore, I would cherish these works. By way of information, I am a news reporter for a television station in Miami, Florida.</p> 
                
                <p>If you care to write, my address is listed below. My best wishes for your continued good health.</p> 
                <closer>
                    <signed>Richard Whitcomb</signed>
                    <signed>Richard Whitcomb</signed> 
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>1140 <hi rend="caps">N.E.</hi> 200 St.</addrLine> 
                        <addrLine>North Miami Beach, Fla 33162</addrLine> 
                    </address>
                </closer>
                    
            </div1>
        </body>
        
